However as far as the crazy math we have going on lemme see if I can clear something up.<br>
Im going ot work this on a 3 month time frame because 1 and 1/2 months is just whacky and for the examlpe I'll be using fear.<br>
45 posting entities, each entity gets to visit fear 2 times for every 3 month period. However some guilds chose to piggyback, granting them 3 to 5 days in that same period.<br>
If the minimum requirement is raised to 36 as opposed to 18 we might be back down to about 35 entities. Lets just be generous and say now we have 30 entities, with each going once per month(hehe I dont wanna get out a calculator), or 3 times per every 3 months period. There is still the same chance of guilds piggybacking (though possibly not as great) and getting their 4 or 5 trips to fear.<br>
Now, lets keep it simple and say entities with more than 66 individuals recieve a 3 days at any one time to alot between fear and hate, as opposed ot the normal 2 (not 3 fear and 3 hate, 3 total). If 10 entities fill this requirement the calendar will have almost as many dates reserved at one time as they would if there were the original 45 posting entities. So, we still have about 40 days posted for fear at all times (assuming the extra 3rd day is used to reserve fear, not hate), however those days are not split among 45 entites, they're divided among 30. The 10 entities with 66+ planeable toons would make up 20 days out of 40 in fear with 20 other entities would comprise the other 20 days (once again this is based on the assumption the extra 3rd day be used for fear and not hate, it would also work with an extra day given for both hate and fear). Anyways, lets do the math now, 20 days taken up by 20 smaller entities while 20 days taken up by 10 larger entities during a 40 day period. So the smaller entities would recieve 2 dates if fear every 2 months and 20 days, a slightly faster rate than the current one. Though not quite as fast were the minimum of 36 institued and everything else left as is, it IS about the same as the current rate, which I have yet to hear any smaller guilds/alliances complain about.<br>
Now, the laerger guilds, comrpising 66+ planeable toons would recieve 5 days in fear every 3 months and 10 days, a far faster turnover than both the current system and the proposed. The effects of piggybacking in this system would be made negligible, 2 guilds of 36 post seperately but attend each others raids...no net gain, they will still be recieving the same amount of dates had the been posting as a singular entity... might I add if all the extra dates were used for fear and not for hate as in the above scenario, all posting entities would recieve 3 days per every 3 months period.<br>
However, if larger guilds are not looking for more planes time than there is no reason to implement a system that correlates number of 46+ toons to dates reservable. However, I am simply proposing it in the interest of fairness and to increase turnaround and epic loot chances asked for by larger guilds while effecting the smaller guilds in NO way (in terms of days reservable) and to curb the effects of piggybacking w/o imposing unwarranted authority on the playing community. <br>
Just so everyone knows I would fall under the category of a SMALLER posting entity, so don't think I'm just blowing smoke up your ass to get more dates <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
Additionally would anyone like to comment on an officer posting page for epic quest loot needed?<br>
<br>
Dios Synsweaver<br>
